It’s just freaking good! Everything. It’s loud and bustling after work on a Friday but they are staffed up and quick! Food is delish. Service is pleasant and prompt. Price is on point. Not a single complaint.

Everything we had was delicious! My husband had the Winter salad with steak and a side of truffle fries. I had the the Tuna Tartar for a starter and the Scallops as my entree. Food was seasoned perfectly and the service was top notch! Definitely going back.

Its was really nice inside and nice to sit at the window looking outside but the food i had better my chicken sandwich  the roll was so hard couldn't eat it and my chicken was really  tough  and really chewy  and my son got a burger and his roll was so hard and my other half her sandwich was ol she had better bread was too hard we won't be back the server barely came to our table to check on us

We loved the complimentary amuse-bouche that started our meal, the Chef’s charcuterie board is giant, the gnocchi and center cut filet was delicious and the palate cleansing sorbet was a great touch before the apple cobbler.

Amazing experience at Firestone's.  The food was exceptional, had glazed short ribs, wife had wagyu beef.  Server, Alice, was extremely friendly, professional, and a pleasure to have.  Dessert was great as well. All in all, wonderful place to have a meal and a few drinks!

Christmas Eve dinner with our group of 6. A very pleasant atmosphere and a great meal too. Tables are properly spaced for Covid19 restrictions and luckily we can still eat indoors.

Delicious food! The Mussels were delicious and savory. The chef brought us a tasty clam cheesecake treat and a mixed berry sorbet between courses that was absolutely scrumptious. Wait staff was extremely friendly. Wife got the Scallops and we were pleased with the serving size. I got the duck and it was just what I was looking for. Definitely recommend and hope to make it back again soon!

Food is amazing here!!  Reservations can be made via OpenTable.  Highly recommend the crab dip, scallops and steak.  Service was really great!  On top of the delicious food my friends and I ordered, our server brought out a few small things complimentary from the restaurant which was so sweet!

May be we will do dessert next time, if there is ever another.

Absolutely love this place! From the server to the palate cleansers to the perfectly spaced out cuisine that you would only expect in fine dining all under one roof! My fiance and I ordered the grilled calamari, mushroom ravioli and bacon wrapped filet. 5 stars for incredible consistency. Impeccable service, consistently great food, and special touches.  The dining area is above a busy bar so it can be a bit noisy, but usually feels like a nice busy happy atmosphere and not disturbing.  Some tables overlook Market St. which is fun on a weekend night.  It's fairly expensive, but not Volt level.  It's not a big place, so make a reservation if it's a weekend.  This is and has been our "go-to" spot for a special dinner in Frederick.

So much fun! Unique and tasty cocktails and a terrific brunch menu. Live music too!

Once I get past my need to make tire-rotation jokes (Firestone...get it?),  I'm quite impressed with this old standby on the main drag of Frederick.  It's an interesting space, with downstairs given over largely to the bar and lounge, and dining space upstairs overlooking the bar. Although the pricing and manner are fine dining, the crowd is relaxed and casual.  The portion sizes are fine dining also. Keep in mind there's a separate tavern menu, which is more casual (and much less noteworthy). In fact the only thing we didn't really enjoy was an appetizer ordered from the tavern menu, a grilled pizza that was heavy, chewy, and unimaginative.  What I did like was my crabcake dish. It's not a big crabcake (fine dining), but it's delicious and its accompaniments actually outdo it. The sauce/chorizo/green beans combination of textures and flavor elicit a rare "wow" from my jaded palate.  Nice, professional service. Unobtrusive and completely on top of things. During a recent dinner, we received an amuse bouche between courses, a pleasing touch.
Fantastic service and absolutely delicious food. Would highly recommend the seared tuna sandwich!

I had a birthday bruch at Firestone's Culinary Tavern. There was a delay in seating us (we had reservations at 2pm and were seated closer to 2:30) but the manager apologized and comped us appetizers, so all is forgiven! They also gave me a free birthday dessert, their angel food cake with blueberries and lemon curd (which was great). All the food we had was excellent, especially the croque madame. I will say the restaurant is not very accessible to people in wheelchairs or who have trouble with stairs -- most of the seating is up a flight of stairs, and I did not see an elevator. A family member of mine is on dialysis and easily winded and had trouble with the stairs. The bathrooms are cramped and would be difficult if you were in a wheelchair, using a mobility device, or needed an aide. But I do recommend this restaurant if none of those things are a concern of yours!

Entry and seating  My Wife and I had a 6pm reservation. We arrived 10 minutes early and were warmly greeted by the hostess. Our table was open and we were seated promptly. In short order our server welcomed us and had our waters filled. She was friendly and well spoken. Once the water was filled she excused herself. *Service missed opportunity - 1. Remind servers to give their names - allows for a more intimate dining experience 2. Ask if it is the guests first meal with the establishment. Opportunity to provide the customer small tokens to set a precedent and a value to their patronage. Example - complimentary cup of coffee, a desert to share or as simple as here's a coupon for 10% off your next meal. 3. Brief overview of the menu, wines & spirits A great opportunity to push a regional/seasonal favorite and showcase the servers knowledge of the Chefs menu as well engaging the customer.  Ordering and drinks -  Once our server returned, she answered our questions, and took our appetizer and drink orders. The cocktail, The Firepit was delicious. Properly mixed and served within minutes of preparation. The Malbec was fresh and served at the right temperature.  Appetizers -  Ahi Tuna Tartare - Generous portion, fresh with unpretentious presentation. Taste, texture and smell was perfect.  Crab dip - Generous portion, fresh but lacked any presentation to celebrate a Maryland staple food. Bread was a little past its prime. The crab dip was proper temperature, proper consistency and was delicious.  Oysters on the half shell - Server did not know where the oysters were harvested or any other info. They oysters were clearly two different types. Their shells were filled with brine leaving the oyster on the sloppy side as opposed to firm . The oyster pan was overfilled with ice resulting in picking up ice that fell from the tray repeatedly. We did not find the quality to equal their price at $2 per oyster.  Dinner - Lamb shank - Generous portion, simple and approachable presentation. The protein was tender, flavorful and at proper temperature. The meat was dry in areas though. It is a quality piece of meat but did not quite hit the mark on value to quality ratio. A tad overpriced.  18oz aged cowboy steak - Odered rare. Presentation was a bust. The protein was served on a bed of asparagus and red peppers in a blue cheese sauce. The disconnect was the large unruly pile of potatoe straws on top of the steak. The steak was properly prepared as ordered and burst with flavor. The Chef certainly understands steak and simple seasoning. It was very good as were those misfit potatoe straws and veggies. However, at $45 it too failed to meet the quality to value ratio.  Concerns: 1. I ordered a jalepeno margarita but was informed that drink wasn't available on The Tavern side, only in the raw bar that was literally on the other side of the wall. Absurd that a patron couldn't be accomodated for such a silly reason. 2. I asked to speak with the manager to see if the drink request could be filled with their approval. She promptly reported to our table and asked how she could help. We do not know her name because again it was not offered. She explained that the request could not be filled because the jalepeno infused tequila was only stocked at the raw bar not the dining room bar. Without any further discussion or even an apology she was off. Along with remedial customer service lessons I'd also suggest a more professional attire or at least one that denotes her management status. Atmosphere is more than decor. These small details are what set you apart in a crowded competitive restaurant field.  The food by in large is what made Firestones Culinary Tavern a success during our visit and if our review was based solely on that it would warrant a solid 4 star rating. All the missed opportunities on the service side significantly impacted our overall review and brings it down to 2.8 stars. We are undecided if we will return. Diners should expect more when dropping $170 on dinner for two.  John
